steps.description:
Wear a tutu. It is best bright and even better if multi-colored. Wear striped or colorful tights under the tutu. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/10/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/10/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Wear a skirt made from a range of ties. This type of skirt looks zany, fun and is ideal for a clown design. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b0/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b0/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Clown shoes are usually over-sized and large. Finding real clown shoes might be difficult, so you can improvise in one of the following ways:
Use a normal pair of shoes but add some cardboard ends. Draw large shoe-shaped ends from cardboard, paint them the same color as the shoes, then attach them to the end of the shoes with tape. This will only last one wear and if it's raining, they need to be covered in contact paper first, but they should suffice for a single wear. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d7/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d7/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use shoes that are a size or two larger than your normal shoes, preferring sandshoes, sneakers or other soft sports/beach style shoes. Tie them up tightly so that they don't come off your feet. Walk with care and do not run in them. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ae/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ae/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Check online for clown shoe sales. There might be an affordable pair. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/22/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/22/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Wear ankle boots. Boots look bigger than shoes naturally, so they are ideal in place of the standard clown shoes. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c6/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c6/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-8Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Paint a really large red mouth. It can either be smiling or frowning; the main thing is that it be larger than your actual lips. Be sure to really exaggerate the smile or frown, by making the ends of your mouth turn right up or right down. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Paint red rosy cheek circles, with red face paint. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/36/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/36/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use black face paint to make your eyes much larger or more obvious. You could paint black circles around them, paint really long eyelashes, darken your eyebrows to make them stand out, etc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/eb/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/eb/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add other features as wished. For example, you might add a tear or cross sections through each of your eyes. Love hearts make a cute and more upbeat look. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Clown-Costume-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
